commit 1a38f811a78ecde501185124416ff83e6bedd5bb
Author: Corey Thompson <coreyt@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 24 15:30:14 2026 -0500

    fix(security/python): add uv.lock; idna advisory addressed (CVE-2024-3651)
    
    Advisory CVE-2024-3651 / GHSA-jjg7-2v4v-x38h: idna.encode() bypass for
    internationalized domain names (medium severity). Dependabot alert
    references python/uv.lock (path computed before uv.lock existed in repo).
    
    uv.lock generated via 'uv sync --extra dev'; idna is NOT a transitive
    dependency of the current Python SDK environment (deps: pytest, hypothesis,
    ruff, pyright only). uv lock --upgrade-package idna confirms no idna
    resolution needed — 15-package resolution contains no idna entry.
    
    Verified: pip-audit --path .venv → 0 vulnerabilities. Zero fathomdb API
    surface impact (transitive dev-tool dependency investigation; idna not
    present).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

 src/python/uv.lock | 246 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 246 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 src/python/uv.lock

---PATCH---
commit 1a38f811a78ecde501185124416ff83e6bedd5bb
Author: Corey Thompson <coreyt@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 24 15:30:14 2026 -0500

    fix(security/python): add uv.lock; idna advisory addressed (CVE-2024-3651)
    
    Advisory CVE-2024-3651 / GHSA-jjg7-2v4v-x38h: idna.encode() bypass for
    internationalized domain names (medium severity). Dependabot alert
    references python/uv.lock (path computed before uv.lock existed in repo).
    
    uv.lock generated via 'uv sync --extra dev'; idna is NOT a transitive
    dependency of the current Python SDK environment (deps: pytest, hypothesis,
    ruff, pyright only). uv lock --upgrade-package idna confirms no idna
    resolution needed — 15-package resolution contains no idna entry.
    
    Verified: pip-audit --path .venv → 0 vulnerabilities. Zero fathomdb API
    surface impact (transitive dev-tool dependency investigation; idna not
    present).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

