\n    {\n      \"id\": \"python-native-not-prebuilt-in-fresh-worktree\",\n      \"severity\": \"operational-note\",\n      \"description\": \"Fresh worktree at /tmp/fdb-... had no built native fathomdb extension; `bash scripts/agent-test.sh` collected 7 ImportError on `import fathomdb`. Resolved by `pip install -e src/python/` per feedback_python_native_build memory. Built wheel fathomdb-0.6.0rc1-cp310-abi3-linux_aarch64. Tests pass after install.\",\n      \"orchestrator_decision_required\": \"none — pre-existing worktree bootstrap pattern.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"next_step_for_orchestrator\": \"Cherry-pick e3f1822 onto 0.6.0-rewrite. Then decide HEAD-on-main blocker: either patch verify-release-gates.sh to allow 0.6.0-rewrite for RC cycle, or merge 0.6.0-rewrite → main before tagging. Then run dispatch dry-run rehearsal (`gh workflow run release.yml -f dry_run=true --ref 0.6.0-rewrite`), record per-tier results, present HITL approval gate per 12-RC1 Sub-3 checklist before the real `git push origin v0.6.0-rc.1`.\"\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
