 1.419},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 184.4, \"concurrent_ms\": 121.5, \"bound_ms\": 34.6, \"speedup\": 1.518},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 181.1, \"concurrent_ms\": 120.0, \"bound_ms\": 34.0, \"speedup\": 1.509}\n    ],\n    \"sequential_ms\": 182.2,\n    \"concurrent_ms\": 121.5,\n    \"bound_ms\": 34.2,\n    \"speedup\": 1.509,\n    \"stddev_concurrent\": 4.8,\n    \"n\": 5\n  },\n  \"delta_concurrent_pct\": 5.65,\n  \"delta_sequential_pct\": 0.11,\n  \"delta_speedup_pct\": -4.48,\n  \"ac017_status\": \"green\",\n  \"ac018_status\": \"green\",\n  \"ac018_drain_ms_after\": 220,\n  \"ac020_passes_5_33x\": false,\n  \"ac020_passes_packet_1_25_margin\": false,\n  \"ci_cross_platform\": \"deferred:only local aarch64-linux build tested; libsqlite3-sys-0.28.0 build.rs LIBSQLITE3_FLAGS path is architecture-neutral (-D/-U flags only, no c_char hardcoding introduced); route should work on x86_64-linux and darwin-arm64 but not CI-verified in this run\",\n  \"ci_platforms_passed\": [\"aarch64-linux\"],\n  \"ci_platforms_failed\": [],\n  \"reviewer_verdict\": \"PENDING\",\n  \"phase78_review_verdict\": \"PENDING\",\n  \"deployment_mode_question\": \"C.1 REVERT confirms bundled-libsqlite3-sys compile flag approach works mechanically (THREADSAFE=2 confirmed by tests) but does not improve concurrency. The deployment-mode question (whitepaper §8 q3) remains: THREADSAFE=2 would require bundled-only commitment (system SQLite on most distros is THREADSAFE=1). Since C.1 shows no perf benefit, this question is moot until a future experiment re-examines it; for now the project stays THREADSAFE=1 (default bundled) without requiring a bundled-only deployment posture.\",\n  \"loc_added\": 0,\n  \"loc_removed\": 0,\n  \"files_changed_pre_revert\": [\n    \".cargo/config.toml\",\n    \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml\",\n    \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/compile_options.rs\"\n  ],\n  \"files_changed\": [\n    \"dev/plan/runs/C1-evidence-compile-options.txt\",\n    \"dev/plan/runs/C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-output.json\"\n  ],\n  \"commit_sha\": \"none\",\n  \"data_for_pivot\": \"THREADSAFE=2 rebuild applied correctly and verified (sqlite3_threadsafe()==2, PRAGMA THREADSAFE=2, two independent green tests before revert). AC-020 concurrent median 121.5ms vs A.1 115ms (+5.65%) — essentially flat, speedup 1.509x vs 1.58x (-4.48%). Kill criterion MET: C.1 was the strongest compile-time mutex intervention (replaces B.1+B.3 stacked per update log); result is within ±5% of baseline (barely outside at +5.65%, within 1.2 stddev). The A.2 hot symbols (__aarch64_swp4_rel, __aarch64_cas4_acq, ___pthread_mutex_lock) are NOT SQLite compile-time threading mutexes — they are unaffected by SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2. Promote D.1 (per-connection lookaside or alt reader architecture). Reverting C.1 cleanly restores A.1 baseline state; Cargo.lock unchanged.\",\n  \"unexpected_observations\": \"sqlite3_threadsafe() confirmed returning compile-time value (2 after rebuild, as A.3 predicted). The THREADSAFE=2 compile flag was applied unambiguously via -USQLITE_THREADSAFE -DSQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 (undefine-before-redefine pattern matching libsqlite3-sys bundled-nosafety idiom). No new c_char/i8/u8 FFI hardcodes introduced. Pre-existing compile errors in tests/compatibility.rs, tests/cursors.rs, tests/lifecycle_observability.rs (A.0 baseline) unchanged. MUTEX_PTHREADS still appears in compile_options with THREADSAFE=2 — this is expected; MUTEX_PTHREADS is the mutex implementation backend, not the threading mode. The per-connection mutex is still physically present in the binary at THREADSAFE=2 (it is only disabled at THREADSAFE=0 or with SQLITE_NO_MUTEX). This may partially explain why the perf is flat: THREADSAFE=2 removes only the global allocator/pcache serialization mutex, not the per-connection mutex which dominates in the ReaderPool read path.\",\n  \"next_phase_recommendation\": \"D1\",\n  \"kill_criterion_status\": \"MET: C.1 concurrent median 121.5ms vs A.1 115ms (+5.65% ≈ flat within noise); speedup 1.509x vs 1.58x (-4.48%). Both THREADSAFE=2 (runtime path, B.1) and THREADSAFE=2 (compile-time path, C.1) show no improvement. Per A.4 kill criterion: mutex track is wrong — promote D.1 (per-conn lookaside, alt reader architecture, or WAL-pager contention investigation).\"\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":783,"cache_read_input_tokens":73732,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":783},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8996a1e6-f0cf-41f6-bd76-ad56a5a9b42e","uuid":"e9fe3af7-6fdc-4c28-88af-ee9aead91e57"}
